JOHANNESBURG - The Trek4Mandela team had a surprise guest on Wednesday. The climbers got to meet former first lady Graça Machel on their flight to Tanzania. Graca Machel meets with #Trek4Mandela team members in Dar es Salaam. Team starts climbing tomorrow. @eNCA pic.twitter.com/30fdZYydwP She's offered her support, saying the group was climbing for a great cause. READ: Trek4Mandela team sets off for annual Kilimanjaro climb Machel also had a brief chat with Letshego Zulu, whose husband Gugu died on last year's expedition. The team will start climbing on Friday. They're hoping to summit Kilimanjaro on Madiba's birthday. eNCA